1
00:00:00,113 --> 00:00:01,668
Let’s start working with the bread
so it’s ready when you need it…

2
00:00:01,693 --> 00:00:02,693
There you go.

3
00:00:02,709 --> 00:00:04,689
- Wait a minute, Iskineport, Chard.
- Mmm?

4
00:00:04,789 --> 00:00:07,056
Have you finalized the invitations
for the grand reopening?

5
00:00:07,096 --> 00:00:08,096
Oh my!

6
00:00:08,191 --> 00:00:10,317
So many people want to come!

7
00:00:10,342 --> 00:00:12,837
Every barangay got the invites.

8
00:00:12,861 --> 00:00:15,693
Even the next municipality
has heard about it.

9
00:00:15,718 --> 00:00:16,804
- Wow!
- They know already?

10
00:00:16,858 --> 00:00:18,177
- Wow, really?!
- That’s awesome!

11
00:00:18,238 --> 00:00:20,005
They want to meet Iskineport.

12
00:00:20,190 --> 00:00:21,483
Really? Why?!

13
00:00:21,517 --> 00:00:23,770
They say you’re really good at making…

14
00:00:23,795 --> 00:00:24,795
Really, now?

15
00:00:26,350 --> 00:00:27,524
- …coffee.
- Wait,

16
00:00:27,548 --> 00:00:29,633
what’s Andres
thinking over there?

17
00:00:29,680 --> 00:00:31,233
What’s going on? He’s in love!

18
00:00:31,274 --> 00:00:33,818
- Don’t overthink it, she loves you!
- What?

19
00:00:33,851 --> 00:00:35,211
- She loves you!
- Yihie!

20
00:00:35,531 --> 00:00:36,531
Ah, I love you guys too!

21
00:00:38,134 --> 00:00:39,941
Good answer, kiddo! Good answer!

22
00:00:40,534 --> 00:00:42,688
He’s always talking to… he’s always –

23
00:00:42,868 --> 00:00:44,021
[screams]

24
00:00:44,081 --> 00:00:45,081
Aga!

25
00:00:45,668 --> 00:00:47,155
Lola Maxi!

26
00:00:47,733 --> 00:00:48,733
Lola Maxi!

27
00:00:48,758 --> 00:00:50,820
This can’t be!

28
00:00:50,844 --> 00:00:54,359
What this fortune ball is saying
could not be possible!

29
00:00:54,384 --> 00:00:56,577
Do you really believe
that fortune ball?!

30
00:00:56,617 --> 00:01:00,236
What’s there to lose if the fortune ball
is telling us good things, right?

31
00:01:00,261 --> 00:01:01,261
Why, what did it say?

32
00:01:01,286 --> 00:01:02,873
What does the fortune ball say?

33
00:01:02,904 --> 00:01:05,064
- It says…
- What?

34
00:01:05,130 --> 00:01:10,960
…the grand reopening of a
business requires the right timing!

35
00:01:11,000 --> 00:01:14,067
That’s not possible, Lola. We’ve
already invited so many people.

36
00:01:14,187 --> 00:01:15,187
We can’t back out now.

37
00:01:15,518 --> 00:01:17,338
- She's right!
- It’d be such a waste of our time.

38
00:01:17,399 --> 00:01:18,959
I guess we’ll just have
to see about it, Lola.

39
00:01:19,040 --> 00:01:20,040
There, look.

40
00:01:20,065 --> 00:01:21,766
See? It’s telling the truth.

41
00:01:21,806 --> 00:01:22,806
It is!

42
00:01:24,101 --> 00:01:25,328
- Oh no!
- Iskineport?

43
00:01:27,340 --> 00:01:28,860
Oh, my! Iskineport…

44
00:01:29,279 --> 00:01:30,279
Hey!

45
00:01:31,445 --> 00:01:39,358
The ball says Kuya Aga
will double our salary, Chard!

46
00:01:39,405 --> 00:01:40,885
What?! Yes!

47
00:01:41,705 --> 00:01:46,226
Kuya Aga! Thank you,
thank you, thank you! Yes!

48
00:01:46,333 --> 00:01:47,820
Let me see, let me see!
Show me! Hang on!

49
00:01:47,852 --> 00:01:48,852
Oh!

50
00:01:49,351 --> 00:01:51,611
That fortune ball is amazing!

51
00:01:51,703 --> 00:01:52,703
Do you see that?!

52
00:01:53,303 --> 00:01:54,583
- Look!
- Show me.

53
00:01:54,608 --> 00:01:55,608
Two…

54
00:01:55,654 --> 00:01:58,494
- Two…
- Two employees are going to be laid off…

55
00:01:58,562 --> 00:02:00,209
- Oh!
- …from work!

56
00:02:00,331 --> 00:02:03,177
Poor Tash and Ate Charls!

57
00:02:03,480 --> 00:02:04,526
What?!
What?!

58
00:02:04,627 --> 00:02:06,195
- You guys should apologize to Kuya Aga.
- Why them?

59
00:02:06,220 --> 00:02:07,264
It’s two people!

60
00:02:07,289 --> 00:02:09,233
- Why them, it’s you two!
- Why us?!

61
00:02:09,320 --> 00:02:10,773
Why would you think
I’m terminating them?!

62
00:02:10,807 --> 00:02:11,807
Fine, I should just fire you, then!

63
00:02:11,876 --> 00:02:14,863
You know what, your fortune-telling
is getting out of hand!

64
00:02:15,006 --> 00:02:16,006
Oh!

65
00:02:16,187 --> 00:02:17,187
Oh my!

66
00:02:17,212 --> 00:02:18,271
- What?
- Stop that!

67
00:02:18,296 --> 00:02:19,370
Why?

68
00:02:19,395 --> 00:02:21,649
Just look at what happened
to Anne and I

69
00:02:21,695 --> 00:02:24,182
because of that fortune-telling!

70
00:03:30,260 --> 00:03:31,260
Orb, Orb!

71
00:03:31,353 --> 00:03:32,353
Tash!

72
00:03:32,378 --> 00:03:34,296
Look at my horoscope for today!

73
00:03:35,501 --> 00:03:37,378
Today is your lucky day!

74
00:03:37,405 --> 00:03:41,711
You’ll meet your soulmate
who you’ve been waiting for!

75
00:03:42,045 --> 00:03:43,165
Oh my god!

76
00:03:43,384 --> 00:03:44,489
[squeals]

77
00:03:44,516 --> 00:03:47,309
I’m so happy for you, Anne!
It’s time!

78
00:03:47,334 --> 00:03:48,334
Do you think he’s handsome?

79
00:03:48,354 --> 00:03:49,363
Of course!

80
00:03:49,396 --> 00:03:52,847
It’s your lucky day, after all!
You’re super lucky!

81
00:03:52,872 --> 00:03:53,872
Orb!

82
00:03:53,897 --> 00:03:55,364
Don’t be too naive.

83
00:03:55,619 --> 00:03:56,966
That’s not true!

84
00:03:57,166 --> 00:03:58,166
Wow!

85
00:03:58,175 --> 00:03:59,289
Thanks, Orb!

86
00:03:59,375 --> 00:04:00,942
You’re so supportive!

87
00:04:01,120 --> 00:04:03,560
When the stars and universe align,

88
00:04:03,760 --> 00:04:05,227
it’s called destiny!

89
00:04:06,050 --> 00:04:08,257
Align? Align?!

90
00:04:09,441 --> 00:04:11,834
It’s all false hope, Orb!

91
00:04:12,629 --> 00:04:13,629
Enough already!

92
00:04:13,654 --> 00:04:14,654
No…well,

93
00:04:14,674 --> 00:04:18,747
Andres kind of has a point.

94
00:04:18,980 --> 00:04:21,220
I don’t mean to interfere,
I’m just saying.

95
00:04:21,580 --> 00:04:22,967
It’s like your Tso K.

96
00:04:23,400 --> 00:04:26,694
He was supposed to go
on a date with your Mom,

97
00:04:26,880 --> 00:04:31,020
but he prioritized his business,
so this is what happened.

98
00:04:31,409 --> 00:04:33,442
Your Mom and I
ended up together!

99
00:04:33,495 --> 00:04:34,822
That’s how it is sometimes.

100
00:04:34,868 --> 00:04:36,075
You never know.

101
00:04:36,680 --> 00:04:37,680
[laughs]

102
00:04:37,705 --> 00:04:38,705
Hey!

103
00:04:39,580 --> 00:04:40,580
- Oh! Tso K!
- BFF!

104
00:04:41,504 --> 00:04:42,504
BFF!

105
00:04:42,599 --> 00:04:43,599
Hi, Tso K!

106
00:04:43,624 --> 00:04:45,011
- Me too!
- What?

107
00:04:45,036 --> 00:04:46,296
I have an example, too!

108
00:04:46,349 --> 00:04:47,415
What is it, now?

109
00:04:47,456 --> 00:04:48,509
It’s just like what
you’re doing!

110
00:04:48,965 --> 00:04:50,059
One asked to loan money,

111
00:04:50,172 --> 00:04:52,172
and he started insulting the person
who loaned him the money.

112
00:04:52,899 --> 00:04:54,772
Of course, the loaner will ask
the loanee to pay up!

113
00:04:55,365 --> 00:04:57,112
Isn’t the loanee the one
on the wrong?

114
00:04:57,172 --> 00:04:58,172
[laughs]

115
00:04:58,502 --> 00:04:59,722
Pay up!

116
00:05:00,064 --> 00:05:01,906
Oh, come on! BFF!

117
00:05:01,931 --> 00:05:02,931
What?

118
00:05:04,323 --> 00:05:09,043
I said I’ll pay! Don’t get too worked up,
we were just teasing!

119
00:05:09,164 --> 00:05:11,396
Okay, well, pay up, then!

120
00:05:11,422 --> 00:05:12,668
Well pay up so
I don’t get worked up!

121
00:05:12,762 --> 00:05:14,955
I told you, I will! Look,
your muscles are so… tense!

122
00:05:15,042 --> 00:05:16,289
Oh, right! Don’t get too –

123
00:05:16,342 --> 00:05:17,851
Kids! Look!
Get a hold of his muscles!

124
00:05:17,876 --> 00:05:18,920
Don’t get too close!

125
00:05:18,944 --> 00:05:20,245
Look at your legs!
It’s something different!

126
00:05:20,270 --> 00:05:21,508
Tso K!

127
00:05:21,533 --> 00:05:22,732
Wow, Tso K!

128
00:05:22,757 --> 00:05:23,757
Amazing!

129
00:05:29,128 --> 00:05:30,128
Who is that?

130
00:05:30,187 --> 00:05:31,727
I have no idea.
When I got here, I –

131
00:05:31,941 --> 00:05:33,221
- Really?
- Really!

132
00:05:33,771 --> 00:05:35,044
Do you know where
she come from?

133
00:05:35,069 --> 00:05:36,510
Look, she's even doing
some fancy actions!

134
00:05:36,827 --> 00:05:37,827
- Hey!
- Hey!

135
00:05:38,507 --> 00:05:40,813
- Who are these three?!
- Who is this?!

136
00:05:40,838 --> 00:05:41,924
What is this?!

137
00:05:41,989 --> 00:05:43,409
What’s happening?!

138
00:05:43,711 --> 00:05:45,551
Oh, I know!
This is… oh, it isn’t.

139
00:05:46,451 --> 00:05:47,505
It’s Goms!

140
00:05:47,625 --> 00:05:49,445
- Hey, it’s Goms!
- Hey, Goms!

141
00:05:49,738 --> 00:05:52,178
Why are you all dressed like that
and who are these people?

142
00:05:52,225 --> 00:05:53,638
Where is Boss Beauty?

143
00:05:53,944 --> 00:05:55,784
That’s Madam Scrub!

144
00:05:55,917 --> 00:05:57,464
Boss Beauty’s cousin!

145
00:05:57,584 --> 00:05:58,584
Where is he, anyway?

146
00:05:58,609 --> 00:05:59,609
He’s sick!

147
00:06:00,009 --> 00:06:02,016
He’s a good fortune-teller!

148
00:06:02,343 --> 00:06:03,462
A fortune-teller?

149
00:06:03,563 --> 00:06:04,743
Iskineport,

150
00:06:05,395 --> 00:06:06,395
maybe…

151
00:06:06,408 --> 00:06:09,041
Let’s have her predict
when we’ll get rich!

152
00:06:09,694 --> 00:06:12,320
Don’t bother.
I’ll predict it for you.

153
00:06:12,374 --> 00:06:14,273
- What?
- You didn’t brush your teeth, did you?

154
00:06:15,838 --> 00:06:18,125
What was that stench, Chard?!

155
00:06:18,178 --> 00:06:19,198
It got to you?!

156
00:06:19,325 --> 00:06:21,565
Well, duh?!
Goms, you smelled it too, right?!

157
00:06:21,678 --> 00:06:23,025
Can’t you smell it there?

158
00:06:23,391 --> 00:06:25,251
But yeah, you guessed it right!
You’re amazing!

159
00:06:25,291 --> 00:06:26,291
- It stinks, doesn’t it?!
- It does.

160
00:06:26,337 --> 00:06:27,337
Hey, hey!

161
00:06:27,797 --> 00:06:30,657
You three, you keep going
around looking like that!

162
00:06:30,877 --> 00:06:32,243
Don’t go too far, alright?!

163
00:06:32,376 --> 00:06:33,476
We’re sorry!

164
00:06:34,056 --> 00:06:35,309
Are you good at fortune-telling?

165
00:06:35,825 --> 00:06:39,366
You know what,
I can see it in you…

166
00:06:39,391 --> 00:06:40,391
Yes…?

167
00:06:40,522 --> 00:06:42,001
When your wife isn’t around…

168
00:06:42,026 --> 00:06:43,026
Yes…?

169
00:06:43,882 --> 00:06:45,908
…you get tempted.

170
00:06:45,933 --> 00:06:46,933
What?!

171
00:06:46,958 --> 00:06:48,074
- With her!
- What!

172
00:06:48,515 --> 00:06:49,515
Oh, my!

173
00:06:49,598 --> 00:06:52,097
Is that why you’re always
staring at me?!

174
00:06:52,163 --> 00:06:53,522
Oh, would you stop
flattering yourself, Mariposa!

175
00:06:53,564 --> 00:06:54,978
It’s fortune-telling,
not fact-checking!

176
00:06:55,011 --> 00:06:58,770
I don’t even know this guy!
And besides, this is just the script!

177
00:06:58,802 --> 00:07:00,688
Sounds true to me!

178
00:07:00,775 --> 00:07:02,235
Okay, I don’t wanna do this!

179
00:07:02,295 --> 00:07:03,615
Okay, then I want it! I want it!

180
00:07:03,722 --> 00:07:04,935
What can you tell me
about my fortune?

181
00:07:04,962 --> 00:07:08,122
Oh you don’t have any, you’re alright.
I don’t even know why you asked.

182
00:07:08,162 --> 00:07:09,615
I actually thought
you were a plant.

183
00:07:10,708 --> 00:07:12,465
I don’t… I don’t have…?

184
00:07:12,490 --> 00:07:13,490
You don’t!

185
00:07:13,515 --> 00:07:15,994
Just be glad
she didn’t guess you’re bald!

186
00:07:17,419 --> 00:07:19,039
You’re too much!

187
00:07:20,126 --> 00:07:22,859
[gibberish]

188
00:07:23,404 --> 00:07:25,763
We call upon the spirit of Roman.

189
00:07:25,803 --> 00:07:30,997
[gibberish]

190
00:07:32,261 --> 00:07:34,360
Darling, how are you?

191
00:07:34,981 --> 00:07:35,987
It’s me, Roman!

192
00:07:38,905 --> 00:07:41,018
Oh, Roman, sweetheart!

193
00:07:41,461 --> 00:07:43,214
I miss you so much!

194
00:07:43,329 --> 00:07:45,765
I miss you so much too,
sweetheart!

195
00:07:47,054 --> 00:07:53,527
Oh, these are our grandkids—
Atasha and Andres!

196
00:07:53,552 --> 00:07:54,987
- Hi, Lolo!
- Lolo!

197
00:07:55,012 --> 00:07:56,045
What’s up, Orb?!

198
00:07:56,307 --> 00:07:57,307
How are you?

199
00:07:57,332 --> 00:07:58,332
I’m good, Orb!

200
00:07:58,882 --> 00:07:59,882
What? Orb?

201
00:07:59,907 --> 00:08:00,907
Orb?!

202
00:08:00,932 --> 00:08:02,558
How did he know that?

203
00:08:02,602 --> 00:08:03,602
Roman?

204
00:08:03,627 --> 00:08:08,347
Oh, sorry.
The connection cut off.

205
00:08:09,207 --> 00:08:10,207
What?!

206
00:08:10,232 --> 00:08:11,232
How could that happen?!

207
00:08:11,639 --> 00:08:13,593
- Uh –
- That cost me P500 already?!

208
00:08:13,618 --> 00:08:17,598
Yeah, it did! It was a long distance call.
Heaven’s line isn’t free.

209
00:08:19,914 --> 00:08:22,102
- You’re overcharging!
- That was P500.

210
00:08:22,127 --> 00:08:24,320
That’s too much!
No promo at all?

211
00:08:24,726 --> 00:08:26,246
Sorry, no promos available.

212
00:08:26,320 --> 00:08:27,320
Would you like to redial?

213
00:08:28,944 --> 00:08:30,164
No way, that’s too expensive!

214
00:08:30,697 --> 00:08:33,980
Thank you!
Please see our client out.

215
00:08:34,005 --> 00:08:35,115
Thank you!

216
00:08:35,140 --> 00:08:36,317
My turn!

217
00:08:36,342 --> 00:08:37,818
I wanna get a reading done.

218
00:08:37,843 --> 00:08:39,883
Come in, darling! Come in!

219
00:08:41,190 --> 00:08:42,803
What do you want to know?

220
00:08:43,323 --> 00:08:46,649
I want to get a reading
about my soulmate-BFF.

221
00:08:46,703 --> 00:08:50,669
I want to know how he looks
and how I’ll meet him.

222
00:08:50,694 --> 00:08:53,600
You want all that for P500?

223
00:08:53,616 --> 00:08:55,399
Fine, give me the cards.

224
00:08:55,424 --> 00:08:57,184
Alright, let’s give you a try.

225
00:08:59,692 --> 00:09:01,531
Okay, your BFF-soulmate.

226
00:09:01,556 --> 00:09:03,829
You wanna know how he looks like.

227
00:09:06,706 --> 00:09:08,419
He has a pointy nose.

228
00:09:09,258 --> 00:09:10,938
My nose is pointy!

229
00:09:13,958 --> 00:09:15,998
His eyebrows are thick!

230
00:09:17,090 --> 00:09:19,039
I have thick eyebrows!

231
00:09:21,615 --> 00:09:22,751
[screams]

232
00:09:22,876 --> 00:09:23,876
What’s wrong?!

233
00:09:24,557 --> 00:09:27,463
Fluffy hair.

234
00:09:30,111 --> 00:09:31,391
- Pointy nose.
- That’s my hair!

235
00:09:31,704 --> 00:09:32,724
Wait, wait, wait a second!

236
00:09:32,749 --> 00:09:34,422
Thick brows. Fluffy hair.

237
00:09:34,447 --> 00:09:36,820
Madame, I have a question.

238
00:09:37,199 --> 00:09:38,259
What’s his name?

239
00:09:39,081 --> 00:09:40,648
His name is…

240
00:09:42,106 --> 00:09:43,106
An...

241
00:09:44,393 --> 00:09:45,627
Anton Lim!

242
00:09:45,800 --> 00:09:46,857
- Anton Lim?!
- What?!

243
00:09:46,882 --> 00:09:47,983
- Anton Lim!
- What?!

244
00:09:48,008 --> 00:09:49,195
What do you mean, Anton Lim?!

245
00:09:49,532 --> 00:09:50,639
You just described me

246
00:09:50,672 --> 00:09:52,025
How is it Anton Lim?!

247
00:09:52,050 --> 00:09:54,356
I mean just the
hair and the nose!

248
00:09:54,381 --> 00:09:57,226
Are you the only one with the pointy
nose, thick brows, and fluffy hair?

249
00:09:57,251 --> 00:09:59,179
Fine, you take over.
Just pay the P500 up.

250
00:10:00,056 --> 00:10:02,549
What am I supposed to do, it was
Anton Lim that came out of the reading.

251
00:10:02,574 --> 00:10:04,574
Sorry, I thought… Anton…

252
00:10:08,362 --> 00:10:09,362
Anton Lim?!

253
00:10:10,759 --> 00:10:13,825
He has a mole here.
He definitely has a mole.

254
00:10:14,413 --> 00:10:16,020
Anton Lim, Anton Lim.

255
00:10:16,421 --> 00:10:17,421
Kuya.

256
00:10:17,446 --> 00:10:18,966
- What is it?
- Excuse me,

257
00:10:19,147 --> 00:10:22,214
do you know anyone named
Anton Lim with a mole here?

258
00:10:22,239 --> 00:10:23,397
Yeah, here. Or here?

259
00:10:23,422 --> 00:10:24,629
I know a Lim,

260
00:10:25,349 --> 00:10:29,802
Gary Lim, the OA comedian.

261
00:10:30,148 --> 00:10:31,148
What’s OA?

262
00:10:31,649 --> 00:10:32,748
O-A.

263
00:10:36,324 --> 00:10:39,466
Sorry, I’m tired.

264
00:10:39,491 --> 00:10:42,231
We’ve gone around the
whole Barangay Singko asking.

265
00:10:42,898 --> 00:10:46,846
I’ve already asked all
my gossip groups, too.

266
00:10:47,283 --> 00:10:48,283
Nothing.

267
00:10:48,308 --> 00:10:51,328
No Anton Lim with a mole here.

268
00:10:51,353 --> 00:10:53,987
Why do you still believe in
these fortune-telling nonsense?

269
00:10:54,496 --> 00:10:55,683
No way!

270
00:10:55,956 --> 00:10:57,376
We’re already here!

271
00:10:58,150 --> 00:10:59,937
But what if he doesn’t exist?

272
00:11:00,350 --> 00:11:03,356
We’ve been looking all
day and found nothing!

273
00:11:03,381 --> 00:11:05,954
No, I really feel
like he’s here.

274
00:11:06,390 --> 00:11:07,390
Hey!

275
00:11:07,429 --> 00:11:08,803
Is this Anton Lim?!

276
00:11:09,736 --> 00:11:11,182
- Orb! Your soulmate…
- Anton Lim?

277
00:11:11,207 --> 00:11:12,600
…was just born.

278
00:11:14,689 --> 00:11:16,563
Are you sure it’s your soulmate?

279
00:11:16,588 --> 00:11:18,640
Maybe it’s your
godchild instead!

280
00:11:21,486 --> 00:11:22,486
Anne! Anne!

281
00:11:22,511 --> 00:11:24,191
- Wait, they’re just joking!
- Orb, Orb!

282
00:11:26,768 --> 00:11:28,054
My love, look at this!

283
00:11:28,079 --> 00:11:32,584
Our sales have gone up so much
thanks to the kids helping out!

284
00:11:32,902 --> 00:11:34,162
That’s true.

285
00:11:34,187 --> 00:11:39,793
I believe that, but it’s still not enough
to pay off our debt.

286
00:11:40,234 --> 00:11:41,547
We still can’t reach the amount.

287
00:11:42,143 --> 00:11:43,703
We still can’t.

288
00:11:44,723 --> 00:11:46,697
You can’t pay your debt again?

289
00:11:47,496 --> 00:11:48,809
Why are you here again?

290
00:11:48,834 --> 00:11:52,111
My love,
don’t talk to Karl like that.

291
00:11:52,217 --> 00:11:53,696
I didn’t mean anything but it.

292
00:11:53,721 --> 00:11:57,861
Isn’t it good that he sees
paying him is a priority for us?

293
00:11:57,886 --> 00:11:58,886
Mmm!

294
00:11:59,601 --> 00:12:00,601
Okay.

295
00:12:01,047 --> 00:12:02,222
- Tastes good?
- Delicious!

296
00:12:02,247 --> 00:12:03,247
Hmmm!

297
00:12:03,272 --> 00:12:05,326
Sales are really up. Look at this.

298
00:12:05,368 --> 00:12:07,228
Look at this one, even!

299
00:12:07,430 --> 00:12:09,823
Come in, come in.

300
00:12:09,848 --> 00:12:10,954
Let me introduce you.

301
00:12:10,979 --> 00:12:12,125
Hey, family!

302
00:12:12,150 --> 00:12:13,963
- Hello, Lola Maxi!
- Come in, come in!

303
00:12:14,503 --> 00:12:15,843
Hi, Lola Maxi!

304
00:12:16,281 --> 00:12:17,281
This lady…

305
00:12:17,306 --> 00:12:19,965
this is… come in, have a seat.

306
00:12:20,452 --> 00:12:24,678
This is Madam… Par…? Pa…?

307
00:12:24,703 --> 00:12:26,794
- Parizcova!
- Parizcova!

308
00:12:26,920 --> 00:12:29,973
She’s Boss Beauty’s cousin!

309
00:12:29,998 --> 00:12:32,345
And she’s great
at fortune-telling!

310
00:12:32,672 --> 00:12:35,239
Mmm?
Uh, Ma…Madam Parizcova?

311
00:12:35,264 --> 00:12:36,264
Yes!

312
00:12:36,518 --> 00:12:39,591
Excuse me, but honestly…

313
00:12:39,623 --> 00:12:41,901
I don’t really… believe
in these fortune-telling things.

314
00:12:42,395 --> 00:12:46,478
No offense. I’m just saying, Lola Maxi,
that I don’t believe in these things.

315
00:12:47,289 --> 00:12:50,623
Don’t worry, I understand.

316
00:12:50,956 --> 00:12:51,956
It’s okay!

317
00:12:51,981 --> 00:12:54,764
Too bad, I could’ve helped you
with your debts.

318
00:12:54,789 --> 00:12:56,947
What?!
How did you know about that?

319
00:12:56,972 --> 00:12:59,374
- Wow!
- Yeah, how did you know?

320
00:12:59,474 --> 00:13:01,014
BFF! She’s excellent!

321
00:13:01,437 --> 00:13:02,816
- She mentioned it!
- That’s right!

322
00:13:02,841 --> 00:13:04,903
Why don’t you try it?
You have nothing to lose.

323
00:13:04,928 --> 00:13:08,367
Get a reading and find out
when you can pay me back!

324
00:13:09,283 --> 00:13:10,990
- You’re too much!
- Come on, let’s take our seats.

325
00:13:11,015 --> 00:13:12,033
Just do it.

326
00:13:12,058 --> 00:13:13,063
Alright, alright. Fine!

327
00:13:13,088 --> 00:13:15,076
But you’re paying
for this, okay?

328
00:13:15,101 --> 00:13:16,740
Fine! Just do it!

329
00:13:16,765 --> 00:13:17,805
Let’s just do it.

330
00:13:18,700 --> 00:13:19,800
Just so I know
when you plan to pay me.

331
00:13:19,825 --> 00:13:21,735
Alright. Let us begin.

332
00:13:21,760 --> 00:13:22,760
Okay, let’s do it.

333
00:13:22,785 --> 00:13:24,719
- We’re starting?
- Yes.

334
00:13:26,020 --> 00:13:27,020
Lights off!

335
00:13:27,507 --> 00:13:28,541
Hey!

336
00:13:29,214 --> 00:13:30,801
Did you see that?!

337
00:13:30,841 --> 00:13:32,681
See, I told you she’s good!

338
00:13:32,781 --> 00:13:34,274
Fog machine ready?

339
00:13:34,299 --> 00:13:35,299
Ready!

340
00:13:35,324 --> 00:13:36,337
Fire!

341
00:13:38,420 --> 00:13:40,560
Let’s hold hands...

342
00:13:41,226 --> 00:13:42,226
Hold hands.

343
00:13:42,750 --> 00:13:44,937
and close our eyes.

344
00:13:44,962 --> 00:13:46,864
- Close them!
- Close them!

345
00:13:46,889 --> 00:13:50,162
No one opens their
eyes until I say so.

346
00:13:50,209 --> 00:13:51,209
Okay, okay, Madam.

347
00:13:51,249 --> 00:13:53,936
We’re starting!

348
00:13:54,203 --> 00:13:58,916
I can feel the vibrations.
It’s coming through!

349
00:13:59,162 --> 00:14:02,961
A big fortune is coming
to you, Kuya Aga!

350
00:14:02,987 --> 00:14:03,987
What?!

351
00:14:04,012 --> 00:14:06,759
My love, you’ll receive
something great!

352
00:14:06,784 --> 00:14:07,784
Thank you, thank you!

353
00:14:07,809 --> 00:14:09,616
It looks like you’ll be
able to pay your debts!

354
00:14:09,641 --> 00:14:11,553
Wow! That’s great news!

355
00:14:12,194 --> 00:14:13,194
That’s perfect!

356
00:14:16,042 --> 00:14:19,414
Can you feel the luck?

357
00:14:20,268 --> 00:14:21,694
Why does her voice
sound different?

358
00:14:21,719 --> 00:14:24,371
It looks like you’ll pay
your debt tomorrow!

359
00:14:24,396 --> 00:14:25,467
- Oh wow!
- Yes!

360
00:14:25,503 --> 00:14:26,623
Thank you, thank you!

361
00:14:26,648 --> 00:14:27,654
BFF, you’re finally
gonna be able to pay!

362
00:14:27,679 --> 00:14:28,694
Yes, thank you!
Thank you very much!

363
00:14:28,719 --> 00:14:30,350
Yes, BFF! Yes!

364
00:14:30,430 --> 00:14:31,729
Isn’t that good news?

365
00:14:31,757 --> 00:14:32,963
Yes, it is!

366
00:14:33,089 --> 00:14:35,262
At least you’ll be able
to pay your debt!

367
00:14:35,287 --> 00:14:39,349
That’s amazing news!
She told you herself, it’s done!

368
00:14:39,374 --> 00:14:41,096
- Thank you!
- Thank you, thank you!

369
00:14:41,121 --> 00:14:43,196
Your problem is done!

370
00:14:43,222 --> 00:14:45,441
- That’s right!
- All done!

371
00:14:45,503 --> 00:14:46,523
Thank you! Thank you!

372
00:14:46,776 --> 00:14:47,776
And so is my food?

373
00:14:48,799 --> 00:14:49,820
It’s all done?

374
00:14:49,845 --> 00:14:51,603
- It’s done. We’re done.
- My food is missing-

375
00:14:51,733 --> 00:14:52,963
Thank you for the snack,
it was delicious.

376
00:14:52,988 --> 00:14:53,988
That’s my coffee!

377
00:14:54,425 --> 00:14:56,346
Just believe, and you’ll be able to pay.

378
00:14:56,371 --> 00:14:59,080
Ah, wait, wait, wait, wait.
Uh, Parizcova?

379
00:14:59,105 --> 00:15:00,784
- Yeah?
- I have a reading for you.

380
00:15:00,918 --> 00:15:02,899
- You have a reading for me?
- Yeah?

381
00:15:03,152 --> 00:15:07,336
I don’t think you’ll live long.
Because if I catch you, I’ll kill you!

382
00:15:07,490 --> 00:15:08,490
No, no!

383
00:15:10,116 --> 00:15:11,323
She ate my food!

384
00:15:12,300 --> 00:15:13,962
Tso K, what happened?!

385
00:15:14,589 --> 00:15:15,589
What happened?!

386
00:15:15,756 --> 00:15:16,756
What happened?!

387
00:15:17,206 --> 00:15:19,552
I don’t believe in those
fortune-telling things.

388
00:15:19,577 --> 00:15:20,577
I don’t like it.

389
00:15:20,598 --> 00:15:23,046
Because, you see, first of all,
it’s just a guess!

390
00:15:23,286 --> 00:15:25,045
They’ll tell you,
“This is what will happen.”

391
00:15:25,070 --> 00:15:28,438
Then you’ll believe it
as if it’s real!

392
00:15:28,505 --> 00:15:29,518
That’s how it is!

393
00:15:30,006 --> 00:15:31,006
Oh!

394
00:15:32,719 --> 00:15:33,719
What was that?!

395
00:15:34,605 --> 00:15:35,605
What exploded just now?

396
00:15:36,703 --> 00:15:38,665
- Hey, Iskineport!
- Iskineport, what happened?

397
00:15:38,698 --> 00:15:40,206
- Kuya Aga!
- What happened?!

398
00:15:40,519 --> 00:15:42,078
The oven exploded.

399
00:15:42,725 --> 00:15:44,600
Ah, damn it! The oven exploded?!

400
00:15:44,625 --> 00:15:45,625
Yes!

401
00:15:45,650 --> 00:15:46,703
Why do you look like that?

402
00:15:47,003 --> 00:15:48,003
- This?
- Why does

403
00:15:48,028 --> 00:15:49,383
your face barely
have dirt on it?

404
00:15:49,408 --> 00:15:50,408
This is little?

405
00:15:50,433 --> 00:15:53,419
Just a little dirt on your face,
the oven exploded, and that’s it?

406
00:15:55,876 --> 00:15:56,876
Ah, come here!

407
00:15:56,903 --> 00:15:58,343
Fix yourself up!

408
00:16:03,949 --> 00:16:05,190
There, that’s better!

409
00:16:05,360 --> 00:16:07,207
Game.
The oven exploded?!

410
00:16:07,320 --> 00:16:09,937
And here you are requesting something,
this is supposed to be my last scene.

411
00:16:09,964 --> 00:16:10,964
I’m on my way home!

412
00:16:11,890 --> 00:16:13,976
It’s like I got hit by a grenade!

413
00:16:14,336 --> 00:16:16,243
Let it go –
The oven exploded?!

414
00:16:16,296 --> 00:16:17,296
Yes, it exploded!

415
00:16:17,539 --> 00:16:19,905
I was inside,
and this happened to me.

416
00:16:19,952 --> 00:16:21,272
Is that good enough for you?

417
00:16:21,339 --> 00:16:22,478
- Kuya Aga!
- Oh!

418
00:16:22,624 --> 00:16:24,431
The motorcycle broke down!

419
00:16:24,456 --> 00:16:25,662
Here, have some, too.

420
00:16:25,687 --> 00:16:28,921
The brakes exploded as well!
I even got injured here on my…

421
00:16:28,946 --> 00:16:31,123
Wait, wait, wait, wait!
Go ahead!

422
00:16:31,148 --> 00:16:32,148
I even fell over there.

423
00:16:32,372 --> 00:16:34,193
Do you see it now?
Do you see it?

424
00:16:34,218 --> 00:16:35,875
- Oh?
- That’s what I’m saying!

425
00:16:35,909 --> 00:16:37,858
The oven exploded,
the motorcycle broke down.

426
00:16:37,882 --> 00:16:38,882
Is that luck?

427
00:16:38,907 --> 00:16:40,382
That’s called misfortune!

428
00:16:40,735 --> 00:16:43,115
You know what,
better shut it all down!

429
00:16:43,275 --> 00:16:45,802
We’ll fix all this tomorrow!
Go ahead.

430
00:16:45,840 --> 00:16:46,840
Tomorrow?

431
00:16:47,074 --> 00:16:48,974
Alright, we’ll close the shop.

432
00:16:49,976 --> 00:16:51,070
See that?

433
00:16:51,703 --> 00:16:53,037
How could that be lucky?

434
00:16:53,062 --> 00:16:54,062
You’ve got so many
customers here!

435
00:16:54,087 --> 00:16:55,681
Fortune-telling, luck?
I’m telling you!

436
00:16:57,610 --> 00:16:58,756
Kuya Aga!

437
00:16:58,836 --> 00:16:59,836
Hey, Iskineport!

438
00:17:01,504 --> 00:17:02,504
What’s that?

439
00:17:02,529 --> 00:17:03,529
Here it is.
Where should I put this?

440
00:17:03,554 --> 00:17:04,554
- What’s that?
- It’s not mine!

441
00:17:04,579 --> 00:17:05,779
But I found it here.

442
00:17:05,804 --> 00:17:06,804
Give it to me!

443
00:17:10,858 --> 00:17:11,858
This isn’t mine!

444
00:17:12,684 --> 00:17:13,811
- BFF!
- Yeah?

445
00:17:13,918 --> 00:17:15,351
- I just thought of something.
- What is it?

446
00:17:15,669 --> 00:17:17,742
Maybe that’s the good fortune
the fortune-teller mentioned!

447
00:17:17,767 --> 00:17:19,032
- Right!
- How could…?

448
00:17:19,057 --> 00:17:21,007
How could it be my good fortune
when it’s not even ours?!

449
00:17:21,466 --> 00:17:23,095
The owner will come back for it;

450
00:17:23,142 --> 00:17:24,208
they just left it behind.

451
00:17:24,233 --> 00:17:25,883
Better yet, let’s do this, okay?

452
00:17:25,908 --> 00:17:27,213
I’ll just keep it safe for now.

453
00:17:27,238 --> 00:17:28,380
No, wait. Hold on.

454
00:17:28,405 --> 00:17:30,716
I’ll keep it safe for now, so when the
owner comes back, the bag is here.

455
00:17:30,741 --> 00:17:32,115
We’ll just take a peek, right?!

456
00:17:32,316 --> 00:17:34,156
Let’s just see if there’s anything inside!

457
00:17:34,181 --> 00:17:38,628
Who knows, it might be stacks of cash,
and you can pay off your debt to me!

458
00:17:38,656 --> 00:17:41,209
And why are you deciding,
when we were the ones who found it?!

459
00:17:41,234 --> 00:17:43,179
- He’s right!
- Where did you find it?

460
00:17:44,313 --> 00:17:45,313
Right here.

461
00:17:45,340 --> 00:17:46,513
- In the bakeshop?
- Yeah.

462
00:17:46,540 --> 00:17:47,880
- And who owns the bakeshop?
- You do!

463
00:17:49,213 --> 00:17:52,619
Okay. Loud and clear enough.
Easy peasy, yeah?

464
00:17:53,440 --> 00:17:54,833
It’s really that simple.

465
00:17:55,628 --> 00:17:56,628
What a waste!

466
00:17:56,653 --> 00:17:58,233
- What a waste!
- We should’ve opened it!

467
00:17:58,320 --> 00:18:01,212
But he didn’t want to.
Besides, I’m not… [gibberish]

468
00:18:04,955 --> 00:18:05,955
Hmm?

469
00:18:17,728 --> 00:18:18,728
My love,

470
00:18:18,753 --> 00:18:20,136
- Lola Maxi.
- whose bag is that?

471
00:18:20,314 --> 00:18:21,614
I don’t know.

472
00:18:21,661 --> 00:18:24,404
Someone left it in our bakery.
Maybe a customer.

473
00:18:24,429 --> 00:18:25,429
Oh no!

474
00:18:25,534 --> 00:18:29,175
Maybe that’s the fortune
the fortune-teller mentioned!

475
00:18:29,228 --> 00:18:30,275
Oh no, no.

476
00:18:30,981 --> 00:18:33,268
That doesn’t seem right, Lola Maxi.

477
00:18:33,475 --> 00:18:39,074
Aga’s fortune would mean someone else’s
misfortune if we claim their bag.

478
00:18:39,195 --> 00:18:42,154
- You’re right!
- It doesn’t seem right, Lola Maxi.

479
00:18:42,179 --> 00:18:43,179
You’re right, my love!

480
00:18:43,204 --> 00:18:44,344
You’re right, my loves!

481
00:18:44,598 --> 00:18:45,858
You know why?

482
00:18:46,231 --> 00:18:48,884
Because what if the person
who left this is a student?

483
00:18:49,411 --> 00:18:52,084
Or a customer who’s
an employee here,

484
00:18:52,144 --> 00:18:53,691
and what’s inside is important?

485
00:18:53,784 --> 00:18:55,264
Why would we take it?

486
00:18:55,663 --> 00:18:57,244
Well, if you don’t want it,
I’ll take it!

487
00:18:57,269 --> 00:18:58,537
Oh no, wait! Lola Maxi!

488
00:18:58,562 --> 00:18:59,743
Lola Maxi, don’t do this.

489
00:18:59,744 --> 00:19:03,144
Lola Maxi, that’s what I’m saying—
this is why I don’t like fortune-telling.

490
00:19:03,504 --> 00:19:07,751
Because now you’re thinking this
bag is the treasure they mentioned.

491
00:19:07,844 --> 00:19:09,564
Just because the
fortune-teller said it,

492
00:19:09,588 --> 00:19:11,777
you’re connecting everything.

493
00:19:11,802 --> 00:19:14,511
You think this is for me.

494
00:19:14,757 --> 00:19:16,697
That’s wrong, Lola Maxi, okay?

495
00:19:16,850 --> 00:19:18,490
Here’s what we’ll do instead, okay?

496
00:19:18,897 --> 00:19:21,469
We’ll surrender this to
the barangay tomorrow.

497
00:19:22,783 --> 00:19:24,897
- No.
- That’s actually a great idea.

498
00:19:25,117 --> 00:19:26,117
Isn’t it?

499
00:19:26,617 --> 00:19:30,043
No, but it’s better
if I just keep it!

500
00:19:30,142 --> 00:19:32,782
Okay, you can. There’s no problem
if you’re the one keeping it.

501
00:19:32,859 --> 00:19:34,312
- Yes!
- Alright, Lola Maxi.

502
00:19:34,412 --> 00:19:36,632
Of course! This is Lola Maxi
you’re talking to!

503
00:19:36,908 --> 00:19:38,041
Alright, thank you!

504
00:19:38,066 --> 00:19:39,395
We’re gonna go to sleep!

505
00:19:39,494 --> 00:19:40,494
Okay!

506
00:19:40,519 --> 00:19:41,519
Mm-mm!

507
00:19:41,544 --> 00:19:45,084
- I am! I am just guarding it!
- Good night, Lola Maxi!

508
00:19:46,397 --> 00:19:48,870
Alright! Go to sleep.

509
00:19:58,693 --> 00:20:00,160
- Lola Maxi!
- Lola Maxi!

510
00:20:00,571 --> 00:20:03,358
I am! I am just guarding it!

511
00:20:04,239 --> 00:20:05,772
- Cheers, cheers!
- Cheers!

512
00:20:05,824 --> 00:20:07,051
Go on, chug it.

513
00:20:07,760 --> 00:20:10,486
That’s what your Kuya
Iskineport and I do!

514
00:20:10,511 --> 00:20:12,281
- That’s it!
- Keep going, Andres!

515
00:20:12,306 --> 00:20:14,180
That’s called “bottoms up!”

516
00:20:14,205 --> 00:20:16,871
Yes! Yes, yes, yes!

517
00:20:17,058 --> 00:20:18,178
Third round!

518
00:20:19,445 --> 00:20:20,887
- We really should…
- Mmm?

519
00:20:20,912 --> 00:20:22,452
…have opened Kuya Aga’s bag.

520
00:20:22,477 --> 00:20:23,856
That’s my line too.

521
00:20:24,485 --> 00:20:25,725
We really should have!

522
00:20:25,778 --> 00:20:31,664
We should’ve checked
the bag, Iskineport,

523
00:20:32,537 --> 00:20:34,476
to find out what’s inside –

524
00:20:34,837 --> 00:20:36,035
- What’s in the bag?
- Yes.

525
00:20:36,060 --> 00:20:37,703
Maybe that’s Kuya Aga’s fortune.

526
00:20:37,731 --> 00:20:39,272
That’s correct.
I couldn’t imagine if it were.

527
00:20:39,297 --> 00:20:43,530
But you know,
we should’ve opened it to see…

528
00:20:48,310 --> 00:20:51,248
Buddy, are you okay?

529
00:20:51,382 --> 00:20:52,382
Hmm!

530
00:20:52,782 --> 00:20:54,575
There you go!

531
00:20:55,002 --> 00:20:56,002
Oh!

532
00:20:56,088 --> 00:20:58,342
Andres, stop drinking so much!

533
00:20:58,433 --> 00:21:00,679
Kuya Aga might scold us later!

534
00:21:02,093 --> 00:21:03,147
Alright, cheers, cheers!

535
00:21:08,901 --> 00:21:10,135
You know, Andres…

536
00:21:10,160 --> 00:21:11,160
What?

537
00:21:11,162 --> 00:21:14,315
…I think you look jealous!

538
00:21:14,340 --> 00:21:16,253
Your face shows it!

539
00:21:16,286 --> 00:21:18,332
Me? Jealous?

540
00:21:18,357 --> 00:21:19,357
Yeah!

541
00:21:19,382 --> 00:21:20,762
Why would I be jealous?

542
00:21:21,286 --> 00:21:25,351
I don’t even know why you’d be—
because I heard that…

543
00:21:26,123 --> 00:21:28,287
Anne…

544
00:21:28,312 --> 00:21:29,312
What about Anne?

545
00:21:29,337 --> 00:21:32,217
…Anne. Wait,
let me drink first, okay?

546
00:21:34,947 --> 00:21:40,866
Anne! She’s looking for her…
sweet of your dreams?!

547
00:21:40,891 --> 00:21:41,891
Yes!

548
00:21:42,815 --> 00:21:44,521
According to the fortune-teller?

549
00:21:44,715 --> 00:21:47,261
Her… sweet… soulmate?

550
00:21:47,328 --> 00:21:49,088
- Soulmate?!
- Soulmate?!

551
00:21:50,012 --> 00:21:51,012
Bottoms up!

552
00:21:51,892 --> 00:21:54,028
How are you?
What’s up with you and Anne?

553
00:21:54,276 --> 00:21:55,276
Are you two a thing?

554
00:21:55,436 --> 00:21:56,569
No, no.

555
00:21:58,432 --> 00:22:00,505
Anne is just my Orb!

556
00:22:00,552 --> 00:22:01,659
She’s just a friend.

557
00:22:01,709 --> 00:22:02,718
Really? Just a friend?

558
00:22:02,743 --> 00:22:04,019
And I’m not jealous, okay!

559
00:22:04,291 --> 00:22:06,098
Honestly, I’m not jealous!

560
00:22:06,352 --> 00:22:09,871
Hey! He says he’s not jealous!
Let’s try that again!

561
00:22:09,925 --> 00:22:12,078
Your face says you’re jealous!

562
00:22:12,217 --> 00:22:14,030
Why, why?

563
00:22:14,111 --> 00:22:16,030
I’m good-looking.
Am I ugly? Am I ugly?

564
00:22:16,071 --> 00:22:18,197
Compared to Chard and me,

565
00:22:18,419 --> 00:22:21,186
you don’t stand a chance
in terms of handsomeness.

566
00:22:21,211 --> 00:22:23,457
We’re ahead in
being ugly, buddy!

567
00:22:23,482 --> 00:22:25,243
No! We’re handsome!

568
00:22:25,297 --> 00:22:26,890
You’re already confessing,
you’re drunk!

569
00:22:26,924 --> 00:22:28,097
I’ve already let myself go!

570
00:22:28,917 --> 00:22:30,850
How much have I drunk?

571
00:22:40,445 --> 00:22:41,445
Orb!

572
00:22:45,776 --> 00:22:47,276
You’re so drunk!

573
00:22:48,089 --> 00:22:49,089
Why did you drink?

574
00:22:49,114 --> 00:22:50,314
Orb!

575
00:22:50,416 --> 00:22:51,896
Hi, how are you?

576
00:22:53,174 --> 00:22:54,754
I’m just happy for you.

577
00:22:55,007 --> 00:22:56,401
- Happy?
- Yeah.

578
00:22:56,426 --> 00:22:58,019
That’s why you were getting drunk?

579
00:22:58,207 --> 00:22:59,207
What?

580
00:22:59,528 --> 00:23:01,168
Did you think I hadn't noticed?

581
00:23:01,448 --> 00:23:06,222
You’re always annoyed since I had my
fortune told about meeting my soulmate.

582
00:23:06,681 --> 00:23:09,695
Why? Are you jealous?

583
00:23:10,368 --> 00:23:11,368
Huh?!

584
00:23:12,779 --> 00:23:13,899
Jealous?

585
00:23:14,846 --> 00:23:16,271
No way, no!

586
00:23:16,698 --> 00:23:18,285
Then why are you laughing?

587
00:23:19,775 --> 00:23:22,675
Because I have no right
to be jealous, right?

588
00:23:25,346 --> 00:23:26,779
- Ah. Is that so?
- Yes.

589
00:23:26,906 --> 00:23:28,053
What if you did?

590
00:23:28,359 --> 00:23:30,312
- Huh?
- Would you be jealous?

591
00:23:31,592 --> 00:23:32,592
Huh?

592
00:23:33,772 --> 00:23:34,772
Jealous?

593
00:23:44,941 --> 00:23:46,007
Hey!

594
00:23:50,123 --> 00:23:51,123
You startled me!

595
00:23:51,777 --> 00:23:54,670
Looks like you’re going to
swoop in on my niece, huh?

596
00:23:54,717 --> 00:23:57,517
And you’re pretending to be drunk!

597
00:23:57,563 --> 00:23:58,717
No, sir.

598
00:23:59,275 --> 00:24:00,275
[retches]

599
00:24:00,335 --> 00:24:01,335
Hey!

600
00:24:01,335 --> 00:24:02,335
What’s this?

601
00:24:02,401 --> 00:24:04,595
He just sees me
and starts throwing up immediately?!

602
00:24:05,521 --> 00:24:07,028
- That’s something else, huh!
- Orb!

603
00:24:07,128 --> 00:24:09,834
You’re acting like Aga, huh!

604
00:24:11,499 --> 00:24:14,626
Okay, you’re drunk! Go home!

605
00:24:14,953 --> 00:24:17,125
Sorry, I’m a little drunk.

606
00:24:17,305 --> 00:24:18,565
Orb, take care, okay?

607
00:24:18,590 --> 00:24:21,199
I’m going home. Bye, guys!

608
00:24:22,056 --> 00:24:23,790
You’re acting
like your dad, huh!

609
00:24:25,249 --> 00:24:26,503
Oh, worried?

610
00:24:26,723 --> 00:24:28,543
Thinking? Affected?

611
00:24:28,730 --> 00:24:30,456
- No, sir.
- But you look so happy!

612
00:24:30,517 --> 00:24:32,390
And I saw you
holding hands earlier!

613
00:24:33,568 --> 00:24:35,474
We’re just friends, Tso K.

614
00:24:35,521 --> 00:24:37,054
Orb my butt!

615
00:24:37,438 --> 00:24:38,438
Go on in!

616
00:24:38,463 --> 00:24:40,456
Or I might just orb
you right here!

617
00:24:41,463 --> 00:24:45,949
I can’t find any Anton Lim
on ApeB or Hinstagram!

618
00:24:46,401 --> 00:24:48,754
He’s not on TwikTwok either!

619
00:24:49,414 --> 00:24:51,167
It feels like he’s mad at me.

620
00:24:53,067 --> 00:24:56,072
Oh, that’s just how Kuya Andres is.
He’s not mad at you.

621
00:24:56,125 --> 00:24:57,185
Of course not.

622
00:24:58,065 --> 00:24:59,972
But you know, Anne,
if I were you,

623
00:25:00,012 --> 00:25:03,272
I’d have kissed him already
to find out if it’s real.

624
00:25:03,319 --> 00:25:07,701
Hey, we’re supposed to talk
about Anne’s soulmate, right?

625
00:25:07,928 --> 00:25:09,281
Oh, right. Anton.

626
00:25:09,342 --> 00:25:11,741
It’s like that fortune isn’t true!

627
00:25:12,449 --> 00:25:15,547
I mean, even my
soulmate-BFF didn’t show up!

628
00:25:16,024 --> 00:25:17,550
Good morning, guys!

629
00:25:17,684 --> 00:25:19,604
Orb, I have a surprise for you!

630
00:25:19,897 --> 00:25:20,897
A surprise?

631
00:25:21,379 --> 00:25:23,268
Anton Lim, meet Anne!

632
00:25:23,295 --> 00:25:24,535
Uh, I mean, Orb.

633
00:25:24,909 --> 00:25:26,602
Anne, meet your soulmate.

634
00:25:26,627 --> 00:25:27,627
Anton Lim?!

635
00:25:27,652 --> 00:25:28,652
Seriously, Orb?!

636
00:25:29,477 --> 00:25:31,170
Hi, I’m Anne!

637
00:25:31,277 --> 00:25:32,357
I’m Anton.

638
00:25:32,523 --> 00:25:34,017
I live just down the street.

639
00:25:34,042 --> 00:25:35,042
Really?

640
00:25:35,067 --> 00:25:38,103
How have I never seen you before?
Want to grab some fish balls?

641
00:25:38,128 --> 00:25:39,128
- Let’s go!
- Let’s go!

642
00:25:39,153 --> 00:25:41,098
Wait, that doesn’t sound
like part of the fortune?

643
00:25:41,123 --> 00:25:42,543
This is delicious!
It’s my favorite!

644
00:25:42,590 --> 00:25:43,870
They’re so cute!

645
00:25:43,895 --> 00:25:45,376
Wow! So sweet!

646
00:25:45,437 --> 00:25:46,623
Wish I could have that!

647
00:25:46,690 --> 00:25:48,083
But hold on, Andres!

648
00:25:48,223 --> 00:25:52,794
You seemed so negative
about this just yesterday?

649
00:25:54,019 --> 00:25:55,500
No, I’m just happy to help.

650
00:25:55,614 --> 00:25:56,700
I’ll just eat this instead.

651
00:25:59,245 --> 00:26:01,745
They do look compatible,
don’t they?

652
00:26:02,443 --> 00:26:04,223
So, the fortune-teller was right.

653
00:26:07,868 --> 00:26:09,501
- Anne.
- Hey! Wait!

654
00:26:09,842 --> 00:26:11,029
- Hey!
- Looks like—

655
00:26:11,054 --> 00:26:12,201
That’s rude!

656
00:26:15,359 --> 00:26:16,790
- Oh, my!
- Hold him down!

657
00:26:18,017 --> 00:26:21,141
Anton!
Anton! Hold him down!

658
00:26:21,861 --> 00:26:22,861
Anton!

659
00:26:22,875 --> 00:26:24,208
Anton! Get out of here!

660
00:26:24,513 --> 00:26:26,300
- Anton!
- Don’t come back!

661
00:26:28,196 --> 00:26:29,969
Andres, are you hurt?

662
00:26:30,843 --> 00:26:31,883
Are you okay, Orb?

663
00:26:33,307 --> 00:26:35,380
I’m fine, I’m fine.
I’m all good.

664
00:26:36,221 --> 00:26:38,267
Is Andres hurt?

665
00:26:42,794 --> 00:26:44,114
Where’s the bag?

666
00:26:45,138 --> 00:26:46,138
- Lola Maxi!
- What?

667
00:26:48,079 --> 00:26:49,486
So, we’re clear on this, right?

668
00:26:50,231 --> 00:26:52,754
If we find the bag
and it’s full of money,

669
00:26:52,778 --> 00:26:54,179
we split it evenly, okay?

670
00:26:55,478 --> 00:26:57,398
- Even split!
- Even split, like siblings!

671
00:26:57,423 --> 00:26:59,509
Even split.

672
00:26:59,982 --> 00:27:01,136
Even split! Promise!

673
00:27:06,605 --> 00:27:07,605
Someone’s here!

674
00:27:07,630 --> 00:27:08,645
- Mmmm.
- What—

675
00:27:08,719 --> 00:27:11,951
Stop peeking,
it’s not like I didn’t see you!

676
00:27:12,900 --> 00:27:15,173
- What are you doing here?!
- Why are you here?!

677
00:27:15,240 --> 00:27:16,840
Lola Maxi, why are you here?

678
00:27:17,205 --> 00:27:18,525
We’re here because—

679
00:27:23,450 --> 00:27:25,216
Hey! This is my house!

680
00:27:25,270 --> 00:27:27,763
I live here!
Why are you here?

681
00:27:27,822 --> 00:27:29,717
- Why are you here?
- Yeah.

682
00:27:29,843 --> 00:27:32,516
I know why you’re here,

683
00:27:32,563 --> 00:27:33,603
even if you don’t
want to admit it!

684
00:27:33,636 --> 00:27:34,870
- Just confess already!
- Just tell us!

685
00:27:34,912 --> 00:27:36,752
Come on, why are you here?
Tell the truth.

686
00:27:36,777 --> 00:27:38,132
- Let’s find the bag.
- Alright.

687
00:27:38,219 --> 00:27:40,365
Why? Just tell the truth,
don’t pretend!

688
00:27:40,499 --> 00:27:43,045
Alright, fine, we just want to know
if it’s really money inside.

689
00:27:43,092 --> 00:27:44,725
- I knew it!
- Wait a minute!

690
00:27:44,785 --> 00:27:45,964
Of course, before we do this…

691
00:27:46,036 --> 00:27:48,689
Okay, we’ll split it three ways.

692
00:27:48,743 --> 00:27:50,656
Hey, why just three?
What about me?

693
00:27:50,776 --> 00:27:53,089
Alright, three and a half.

694
00:27:53,187 --> 00:27:54,462
You’re just half a person!

695
00:27:54,487 --> 00:27:55,552
- You’re just half a person!
- Alright, let’s go! Let’s go!

696
00:27:55,579 --> 00:27:57,809
You haven’t grown in ages!
I thought you were just a foot!

697
00:27:57,834 --> 00:27:59,067
- Shh!
- Keep it down,

698
00:27:59,092 --> 00:28:00,113
Aga might wake up. Let’s go!

699
00:28:00,138 --> 00:28:01,578
Okay, we’re here.
You go over there!

700
00:28:01,645 --> 00:28:03,105
I’ll keep looking here.

701
00:28:03,145 --> 00:28:04,694
Maybe it’s near the gas tank!

702
00:28:04,719 --> 00:28:07,899
Come on! Don’t wake him.

703
00:28:08,705 --> 00:28:10,245
I can’t find it, Iskineport!

704
00:28:10,292 --> 00:28:13,132
That’s glass! You can see
what’s inside; it’s glass!

705
00:28:13,157 --> 00:28:14,386
What about underneath?

706
00:28:14,411 --> 00:28:15,411
In the rice cooker?

707
00:28:18,928 --> 00:28:20,614
Is this what you’re looking for?!

708
00:28:21,068 --> 00:28:22,068
Huh?!

709
00:28:22,947 --> 00:28:25,896
Lola Maxi, are you part of this too?

710
00:28:25,921 --> 00:28:28,608
I was just curious!

711
00:28:28,633 --> 00:28:33,650
You should respect Aga’s decision
about what to do with the bag!

712
00:28:34,002 --> 00:28:35,002
Chacha…

713
00:28:35,027 --> 00:28:36,681
Besides, this isn’t even ours, right?

714
00:28:36,706 --> 00:28:38,503
I just want to explain, Chacha.

715
00:28:38,951 --> 00:28:41,035
- We don’t care about what’s inside.
- Ah.

716
00:28:41,075 --> 00:28:44,496
I just want to know
if Aga’s fortune is true.

717
00:28:44,503 --> 00:28:45,504
- Exactly.
- Really?

718
00:28:45,510 --> 00:28:47,125
Why would I care
about the contents?!

719
00:28:47,165 --> 00:28:48,485
- If you don’t care—
- Fine, do whatever you want!

720
00:28:48,554 --> 00:28:51,263
Tso K! If you don’t care, we do.

721
00:28:51,700 --> 00:28:54,433
Because we know
there’s money inside.

722
00:28:54,494 --> 00:28:55,690
Alright, here’s what we’ll do.

723
00:28:55,715 --> 00:28:57,588
Do you really want to
know what’s in this bag?

724
00:28:57,613 --> 00:28:58,613
Yes!

725
00:28:58,614 --> 00:29:00,251
- Let’s go to the barangay! Come on!
- No!

726
00:29:00,324 --> 00:29:03,173
We might get detained
at the barangay!

727
00:29:03,198 --> 00:29:04,198
You’re so exaggerated!

728
00:29:04,213 --> 00:29:05,953
…we’ll all get dragged into it!

729
00:29:06,006 --> 00:29:07,092
This is too much, Aga!

730
00:29:07,119 --> 00:29:11,619
We’ll bring it to the barangay to
open the bag in front of the captain!

731
00:29:11,779 --> 00:29:15,614
Oh, oh, oh, yes?
What kind of K-drama is this?

732
00:29:15,639 --> 00:29:18,519
Ugh! I’m leaving this place.

733
00:29:18,573 --> 00:29:19,779
I’m starving here!

734
00:29:19,803 --> 00:29:21,433
No one even believes
in my fortune-telling!

735
00:29:21,602 --> 00:29:23,322
That’s probably for the best!

736
00:29:23,508 --> 00:29:26,695
So far, none of your predictions
about me have come true!

737
00:29:26,755 --> 00:29:28,141
- Right, Orb?!
- Yes, exactly!

738
00:29:28,762 --> 00:29:33,056
You should just be
called Madam Bola!

739
00:29:33,889 --> 00:29:36,437
Excuse me, I don’t lie.

740
00:29:36,490 --> 00:29:39,330
I honor my
fortune-telling gift, okay?!

741
00:29:39,530 --> 00:29:41,670
Alright, how about this?

742
00:29:42,030 --> 00:29:43,697
If your predictions are true,

743
00:29:44,650 --> 00:29:45,710
you’ll get a kiss from me!

744
00:29:45,884 --> 00:29:46,884
Hey!

745
00:29:46,909 --> 00:29:48,650
Hey, you might
regret that, Orb!

746
00:29:48,697 --> 00:29:49,757
No way, that’s impossible!

747
00:29:50,162 --> 00:29:54,749
You know, I see that
you’re not the type to give a kiss.

748
00:29:55,290 --> 00:29:56,429
You’re right about that!

749
00:29:56,636 --> 00:29:57,930
- Exactly, exactly!
- Right?

750
00:29:59,532 --> 00:30:00,985
OMG!

751
00:30:01,226 --> 00:30:02,600
Really, Beshy?!

752
00:30:02,624 --> 00:30:04,798
Someone sent me a package
from Singapore?!

753
00:30:05,206 --> 00:30:06,947
- Hey!
- How sweet!

754
00:30:07,147 --> 00:30:09,619
Tash, is it food?
Share, please!

755
00:30:09,713 --> 00:30:11,320
I’ll take a keychain, that’s fine!

756
00:30:11,380 --> 00:30:13,213
Or maybe the Merlion,
that works too!

757
00:30:13,240 --> 00:30:14,339
Quiet, guys, please, please!

758
00:30:14,373 --> 00:30:21,206
By the way, how will I know who’s
bringing the package to me tonight?

759
00:30:21,264 --> 00:30:23,486
My cousin will deliver it to you.

760
00:30:24,511 --> 00:30:25,638
Ah! What’s his name?

761
00:30:26,478 --> 00:30:27,485
Anton Lim.

762
00:30:28,971 --> 00:30:30,818
[everyone simultaneously]
Anton Lim?!

763
00:30:31,376 --> 00:30:33,403
[laughter]

764
00:30:38,156 --> 00:30:40,222
Told you so, right? Oh!

765
00:30:46,647 --> 00:30:48,189
See? At least now,

766
00:30:48,213 --> 00:30:50,733
I’ve proven to you that my
fortune-telling is correct!

767
00:30:50,798 --> 00:30:55,548
It’s an honor to show that
Anne really has a soulmate.

768
00:30:56,535 --> 00:31:00,348
Oh! And that someone
named Anton Lim really exists!

769
00:31:00,687 --> 00:31:01,687
Exactly!

770
00:31:01,712 --> 00:31:02,712
You nailed it!

771
00:31:03,027 --> 00:31:07,147
Oh, speaking of which—he’s
almost here, on the way!

772
00:31:08,632 --> 00:31:11,003
But wait, where’s Anne?

773
00:31:11,043 --> 00:31:13,176
Anton Lim is about to arrive,
and she’s not even here yet.

774
00:31:13,223 --> 00:31:15,003
Anne-takes-forever!

775
00:31:15,321 --> 00:31:16,321
Hey, hold on.

776
00:31:16,629 --> 00:31:17,809
Are you okay, Kuya?

777
00:31:18,455 --> 00:31:21,381
Your face looks... not okay?

778
00:31:21,888 --> 00:31:23,374
Are you hurting somewhere?

779
00:31:24,194 --> 00:31:25,287
Maybe your heart?

780
00:31:25,374 --> 00:31:27,427
Nothing, nothing. I’m fine.

781
00:31:27,508 --> 00:31:29,308
- Hey, Tash!
- Anton Lim!

782
00:31:29,676 --> 00:31:33,356
You… you… you have a mole!

783
00:31:33,490 --> 00:31:35,650
- That’s a fly!
- Oh, yeah, there is one.

784
00:31:35,675 --> 00:31:36,675
Alright,

785
00:31:36,915 --> 00:31:37,996
this is for me, right?

786
00:31:38,036 --> 00:31:40,749
Yeah, this is from my
cousin in Singapore.

787
00:31:40,929 --> 00:31:42,483
Alright, I’ll get going now.

788
00:31:42,536 --> 00:31:44,982
Wait, wait, wait! Hold on!

789
00:31:45,411 --> 00:31:48,991
I’ll introduce you to
your future soulmate!

790
00:31:49,016 --> 00:31:50,282
- Soulmate?!
- My soulmate?

791
00:31:50,680 --> 00:31:51,680
Yes!

792
00:31:51,869 --> 00:31:54,742
I’m sure you’ll be best friends,
just like us.

793
00:31:55,902 --> 00:31:57,888
She’s kind, genuine,

794
00:31:58,248 --> 00:32:01,508
and most of all, beautiful.

795
00:32:02,268 --> 00:32:05,548
She’s the best Orb
you’ll ever meet.

796
00:32:05,595 --> 00:32:08,495
Alright. Where’s this soulmate?

797
00:32:09,835 --> 00:32:11,048
Suddenly excited!

798
00:32:11,122 --> 00:32:12,122
Oh, my!

799
00:32:12,739 --> 00:32:14,505
Hi! Anton Lim?!

800
00:32:14,579 --> 00:32:16,519
- I’m Anne!
- So dirty!

801
00:32:16,618 --> 00:32:18,118
I want to be your soulmate!

802
00:32:18,212 --> 00:32:19,212
What just happened?!

803
00:32:21,194 --> 00:32:22,414
Uh, wait a second…

804
00:32:22,494 --> 00:32:23,740
- Why? What’s wrong?
- Well, um…

805
00:32:23,765 --> 00:32:24,987
There’s somewhere I need to be,
and I don’t want to be stuck in traffic.

806
00:32:25,012 --> 00:32:26,320
Huh?! Where?!

807
00:32:26,507 --> 00:32:28,394
Uh, just…somewhere!
Okay, I’ll head out now!

808
00:32:28,427 --> 00:32:30,603
Wait, wait, wait! Don’t go!

809
00:32:40,098 --> 00:32:41,651
You’re something else, Orb!

810
00:32:44,690 --> 00:32:46,977
You’re so happy, Kuya, huh?

811
00:32:47,550 --> 00:32:50,643
Ooooh… someone’s blushing!

812
00:32:51,811 --> 00:32:55,537
Ah, wait, wait, wait!
Don’t celebrate too much just yet, okay?

813
00:32:55,644 --> 00:32:57,558
Remember our deal, Andres!

814
00:32:57,751 --> 00:33:02,371
If I’m right about there
really being an Anton Lim…

815
00:33:02,531 --> 00:33:05,150
- Mm-hmm?
- …I get a kiss from you!

816
00:33:05,769 --> 00:33:07,076
Hey, we agreed on it!

817
00:33:07,875 --> 00:33:11,422
It’s time to collect!
Oh no, Andres!

818
00:33:12,186 --> 00:33:18,072
Oh my gosh, this can’t happen.
Move aside! Move! Where is he? Andres!

819
00:33:21,630 --> 00:33:22,630
Hey!

820
00:33:22,655 --> 00:33:24,922
Those are just plastic and paper!

821
00:33:25,090 --> 00:33:26,682
- It’s empty?
- Yeah!

822
00:33:26,729 --> 00:33:30,242
That’s right!
Aga and I planned all of this!

823
00:33:31,342 --> 00:33:32,755
So we just wasted
our time, then.

824
00:33:32,780 --> 00:33:33,780
True.

825
00:33:33,805 --> 00:33:36,505
This is what we call a social experiment.

826
00:33:36,827 --> 00:33:40,927
To see people’s goodness,
honor, and integrity.

827
00:33:40,961 --> 00:33:45,273
In today’s world, honor seems like a
weakness, but it’s something we value.

828
00:33:45,346 --> 00:33:48,713
Not everyone focuses
on material things, right?

829
00:33:48,999 --> 00:33:51,229
When we do good deeds…

830
00:33:51,254 --> 00:33:52,254
Correct.

831
00:33:52,279 --> 00:33:55,544
…we shouldn’t need an audience.
We don’t have to show it to others.

832
00:33:55,666 --> 00:33:57,006
Right, Tso K?

833
00:33:57,724 --> 00:33:59,624
- What’s with the call out?!
- BFF!

834
00:33:59,664 --> 00:34:01,183
Are you throwing shade at me?

835
00:34:01,208 --> 00:34:02,987
No, not at all!
I’m just saying, when you do good,

836
00:34:03,012 --> 00:34:04,876
you don’t need to show it off.
Just keep it to yourself.

837
00:34:04,901 --> 00:34:09,281
What I don’t understand is
why you did this, Aga and Cha?

838
00:34:09,306 --> 00:34:10,558
- Exactly!
- Well, Lola Maxi,

839
00:34:10,582 --> 00:34:13,167
nobody’s perfect in this world.

840
00:34:13,314 --> 00:34:17,187
And every day,
our integrity gets tested.

841
00:34:17,214 --> 00:34:19,841
See, it’s not just every day.

842
00:34:20,176 --> 00:34:24,669
It’s important in life to always
be like that—kind and good.

843
00:34:24,694 --> 00:34:29,034
Thank you so much, Cha and Aga.

844
00:34:29,589 --> 00:34:34,746
You’ve proven that there
are still good people like you.

845
00:34:34,913 --> 00:34:36,866
You will be blessed.

846
00:34:36,946 --> 00:34:37,946
Oh, thank you very much.

847
00:34:37,974 --> 00:34:39,111
Thank you, Direk Soxie Topacio!

848
00:34:40,061 --> 00:34:41,061
No, no!

849
00:34:41,107 --> 00:34:43,061
That’s Konsi! Konsi!

850
00:34:43,094 --> 00:34:45,381
No, but seriously,
you should thank me!

851
00:34:45,494 --> 00:34:50,454
Without me, BFF, your social experiment
wouldn’t have happened!

852
00:34:50,479 --> 00:34:51,479
Oh?

853
00:34:51,724 --> 00:34:54,117
Wait a second, wait a second!
That’s enough!

854
00:34:54,142 --> 00:34:56,111
- Where are Atasha and Andres?
- I don’t know.

855
00:34:56,153 --> 00:34:57,306
Atasha? Andres?

856
00:34:57,853 --> 00:34:59,374
- Atasha!
- Tash!

857
00:34:59,399 --> 00:35:01,233
- Atasha!
- Atasha!

858
00:35:01,246 --> 00:35:03,201
There they are! There they are!

859
00:35:03,258 --> 00:35:04,858
Oh, what’s that?!

860
00:35:06,164 --> 00:35:07,639
Hey! Time out, time out!

861
00:35:07,664 --> 00:35:08,837
What’s going on?! What’s happening?!

862
00:35:08,862 --> 00:35:09,888
Hold on, hold on!

863
00:35:09,913 --> 00:35:11,278
- There, there, there!
- Me?!

864
00:35:11,303 --> 00:35:12,351
Not you! You wish!

865
00:35:12,376 --> 00:35:13,376
It’s Andres!

866
00:35:13,529 --> 00:35:14,529
The handsome one!

867
00:35:14,554 --> 00:35:18,789
He owes me! He promised that
if my fortune was right, he’d kiss me!

868
00:35:18,814 --> 00:35:19,814
What, really?!

869
00:35:21,219 --> 00:35:23,486
I blew it!
I’m not a good person after all!

870
00:35:23,544 --> 00:35:25,625
What’s going on here?
No hope left!

871
00:35:27,427 --> 00:35:29,893
Are you being
picky? Just kiss me!

872
00:35:33,445 --> 00:35:34,698
Alright, alright!

873
00:35:36,125 --> 00:35:42,071
In struggle and joy,
Pers is first, Pers is the hero!
